<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" class="tborder" width="100%">
<tr>
<td class="tcat"><span class="smallfont"><b>&raquo; Epic 1.0 Walkthrough Part 1</b></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="alt2">
<h1>Cleric Epic 1.0</h1>
<strong>Original walkthrough by Walbort<br>
Updated by Boanerges Thundercry<br></strong>
<hr>
Rather than try to merely update Walbort's walkthrough I decided to make a more linear one that would be easier to follow.<br>
There are 4 general stages:<br>
1. Orb of Frozen Water<br>
2. <a href="index.php?page=epic102">Orb of Clear Water</a><br>
3. <a href="index.php?page=epic103">Orb of Vapor</a><br>
4. <a href="index.php?page=epic104">Orb of the Triumvirate (The final journey)</a><br>
<hr>

<h3>Step 1 (Lake Rathear): Talk to Shmendrik Lavawalker and kill Lord Burgurgle</h3>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul1.jpg" alt="Shmendrik Lavawalker"><br>
<u>Location:</u> Lake Rathetear, loc (3600, 0).<br>
<u>Spawn Timer:</u> Approx. 3 hours<br>
<p><em>Shmendrik Lavawalker says 'Hail, good [your name] !! Be wary near the waters of Lake Rathe! The Riptide goblin king, Lord Bergurgle has been commanding his minions to murder and rob all who come near it! I am here seeking his death but I am afraid I am no match for all of his subjects. I shall reward you greatly for the death of Lord Bergurgle. I simply ask that you bring me his crown as proof.</em></p>
<p style="color:blue">Obviously you can skip the chat but it's important to see where Shmendrik Lavawalker is. You might even want to do the <a href="#optional">optional step</a> first. Once you're ready head to Lord Burgurgle's spawn point an underwater cave Lake Rathetear, loc (2800, 150). Cave entrance loc is (2831, -912, -221). The spawn time is 28 minutes.</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul6.jpg" alt="Lord Burgurgle"><br>
<u>Level:</u> 39-40 Cleric<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> Max hit 97<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> Complete Heal<br>
<p style="color:blue">If you have an Enduring Breath item (or an alt to cast EB on you) you can pretty much do this camp solo. Sit on top of the castle and look down at the goblins (you won't gain agro here). If/when the placeholder spawns start off with a DD spell to pull (they have low agro radiuses so you don't have to worry about assists) and then quickly swim to one of the corners of the cavern. Turn around so your back is to the wall and the goblin will find you (they sometimes cast DD spells). By doing this you reduce the movement that the goblin's melee will do to you and you can likely get in several nukes along with your melee and bashing. Rinse and repeat.<br>
Lord Burgurgle really isn't as much a meleer as he is a caster. Your main problem will be that he casts CH. You might want to get some help fighting him and load up your stuns. He drops Lord Bergurgle's Crown which you need for the next step. The crown can be multiquested.</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul7.jpg" alt="Lord Bergurgle's Crown"><br>
<br>
<h3>Step 2: Hand in the Crown and kill Shmendrik Lavawalker</h3>
<p>(The following occurs when given "Lord Bergurgle's Crown")<br>
<i>Shmendrik Lavawalker shoves the crown into a scorch marked leather satchel and cackles uncontrollably as madness twists his features and flames dance in his eyes. 'You [your name] have reduced the Riptides into chaos! Without a king to keep them in control they will ravage the settlements surrounding this lake! After the slaughter I shall return and easily burn the remainder of the villages and fishing shanties to the ground! None shall escape the fires of the Tyrant!!'<br>
Natasha Whitewater shouts, 'The Triumvirate of Water has decreed your fate, Shmendrik Lavawalker!! I am here to deliver said fate!!'<br>
Shmendrik Lavawalker says, 'I'll slay you like I slaughtered your fellow missionaries! The Triumvirate can not decide the fate of a follower of the Tyrant!!<br>
Natasha Whitewater says, 'Enough!! Your existence has come to an end!<br>
Natasha Whitewater says 'This conflict has been destined by the waters of the Triumvirate!<br></i></p>
<u>Level:</u> 30 Cleric<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> Approx. 1494<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> Very low (2-20)<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> Cancel Magic, Smite, Greater Healing<br>
<p style="color:blue">This fight isn't too hard really. Shmendrik is pretty easy to kill, just keep a stun loaded should he start chain healing himself. The problem here is Natasha Whitewater (as seen below). She spawns when you hand in the crown and walks to where Shmendrik is and begins to attack him. While you don't need anything from Shmendrik's corpse you DO need the item from A Spirit of Flame which spawns upon his death. Natasha will attack that too and if she gets the killing blow the corpse will poof and you'll have to start over. You may want to do the <a href="#optional">optional step</a> first to avoid this problem. Loot the Damaged Crown from the spirit's corpse</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul8.jpg" alt="Natasha Whitewater"><br>
<br>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul4.jpg" alt="A Spirit of Flame"><br>
<u>Level:</u> 40<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> Approx. 3300<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> Moderate (up to 97)<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> None<br>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul5.jpg" alt="Damaged Goblin Crown"><br>
<p>Hail Natasha Whitewater and then hand her the Damaged Crown<br>
(when hailed) <i>Natasha Whitewater says 'The Riptide goblins must have their crown returned to them. If you would be so kind as to give me the crown I will make sure that it reaches them. Hopefully they are capable enough to repair the damage that has been done to it.'</i><br>
(when given the crown) <i>Natasha Whitewater says 'I will have this crown returned to the Riptide Goblins immediately! Should you ever come across an Erudite named Omat Vastsea, give him this sea shell. The waters of Norrath shimmer with awareness of your deeds here today!</i></p>
<p style="color:blue">The spirit isn't too hard to kill either but you might want some help again. The spirit is a fire elemental so it is summoned, therefore you can use your anti-summoned DD spells against it. Natasha despawns when you hand her the crown and you receive back Ornate Sea Shell. Since there are two of these in this quest from now on they will be refered to by their Identify names of Ornate Sea Shell(I) and Ornate Sea Shell(II). This is Ornate Sea Shell(I).</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul9.jpg" alt="Ornate Sea Shell(I)"><br>
<br>
<a name="optional"><b>Optional Step:</b></a> - If you don't want to risk Natasha ruining your camping of Lord Burgurgle then you can simply kill Shmendrik first. He will still spawn the Spirit of Flame upon his death and you can loot the Damaged Crown. You will still need to kill Lord Burgurgle because it's his crown that triggers the event with Natasha.<br>
<br>
<h3>Step 3: Visit Omat Vastsea and Kill the Plasmatic Priest</h3>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul10.jpg" alt="Omat Vastsea"><br>
<p style="color:blue">You can find Omat Vastsea in Timourous Deep, loc (-11567, -2227). To reach him, take the cave entrance at loc (-11530, -3728), then the entrance at (-11336, -1307). Keep in mind that both entrances are underwater. The fastest route here is either to port to South Ro or PoK stone to Freeport and run to Oasis and take the barge into Timorous from there. This goes a lot faster with Levitate since there's a LOT of swimming to reach the island.</p>
<p><i>Omat Vastsea bows deeply. 'I have been expecting you, [your name] . The waters have foretold your arrival. I am High Priest Omat Vastsea of the Triumvirate missionaries. Please feel free to enjoy the quiet solitude of this inn.'<br></i>
<br>
You say, 'who are the triumvirate'<br>
<br>
<em>Omat Vastsea says 'The Triumvirate of Water are: E'ci, the mistress of ice; Tarew Marr, the lord of water; and Povar, the formless master of vapor and mist. We Triumvirate missionaries are granted great divinatory powers and wisdom through our devotion to the Triumvirate and must defend the waters of Norrath from the ravages of the Tyrant of Fire, Fennin Ro.</em><br>
<br>
You say, 'who is fennin ro'<br>
<br>
<em>Omat Vastsea says 'The Tyrant of Fire, Fennin Ro, is the merciless lord of fire in all its forms. The rivalry between the tyrant and the Triumvirate is as old as the gods themselves and is an eternal battle. We witness the struggle every moment of our lives as the Oasis of Marr succumbs to the heat of the surrounding desert and is replenished by the swelling of the Lifire River. That fragile balance between the elements must be maintained but the Plasmatic Priesthood threatens that balance.</em><br>
<br>
You say, 'who are the plasmatic priesthood'<br>
<br>
<em>Omat Vastsea says 'The Plasmatic Priesthood are worshipers of the Tyrant of Fire, but they have been driven mad by their fanaticism and have forgotten the importance of the balance. In their madness they would set the whole world aflame, leaving nothing but lifeless ash.</em></p>
<p style="color:blue">Hand your Ornate Sea Shell(I) to Omat. He will hand you the Coral Statue of Tarew.</p>
<p><i>Omat Vastsea says 'So, you are a friend of Natasha's? That is good to see. She is a very wise and gifted woman. The Riptide goblins have adopted a new king but are still in a vulnerable state until his subjects accept his rule. The Plasmatic Priesthood is aware of the weakened state of the Riptides and has convinced the Fire Peak goblins to strike against them. Although I do not agree with the mannerisms or actions of any goblin clan, such a war would be detrimental to all who are caught in its path. Lord Gimblox of the Fire Peak clan has been meeting with a member of the Plasmatic Priesthood in the Temple of Solusek Ro. Locate the Plasmatic Priest, hand him this statue to hinder his powers, then eliminate him and bring me his robe.</i></p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul11.jpg" alt="Coral Statue of Tarew">
<p style="color:blue">Now you need to head to the Temple of Solusek Ro off of Lavastorm (*Note* the Temple is a Optional download so may need to make sure your patcher options are set to download all optional files). Inside you need to find the NPC named "A Seeker". He is on the second floor of the main room (where the lava flows are). His location is 326,38,29 and he is only up from 9am to 9pm game time (use /time). If he's not up just wait until 9am game time rolls around and he'll respawn.</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul13.jpg" alt="A Seeker/Plasmatic Priest"><br>
<u>Level:</u> 55<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> Approx. 3000-3500<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> Maximum hit 150<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> Complete Heal, Tremor, Annul Magic, Reckoning<br>
<p>You say, 'what plasmatic priest'<br>
<br>
<em>a seeker says 'You speak of things that should not be spoken! It would be in your best interest to leave this temple at once and return to lands less consumed by flame!</em><br>
(when given "Coral Statue of Tarew") <em>A seeker shakes violently as his hand closes on the coral statue and flames dance in the depths of his eyes! The statue begins to emit a reddish glow then shatters in a burst of fire and smoke! The flames in the plasmatic priest's eyes vanish with the explosion and only madness remains! 'The Triumvirate thinks that destroying my spirit of flame will stop me?!! I will kill you all now, the goblins will continue to war, and when my spirit is restored I will ensure that Ixiblat Fer consumes all of Norrath in his flames!!'</em></p>

<p style="color:blue">Once you find the correct NPC (human male as pictured above who responds to "what plasmatic priest") hand him your Coral Statue of Tarew and he will change into A Plasmatic Priest (agro NPC). It's highly recommended you not fight him where he spawns because he uses AE spells which will agro other NPC and if they get the kill you'll have to start over. Instead, hit him and drag him to the zone. This WILL agro other NPCs as they assist the non-agro version. Just root him and zone out. Then, once the others have reset, you can hand in and not worry. Use stuns to keep him from healing himself. He drops Blood Soaked Plasmatic Priest Robe.</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul14.jpg" alt="Blood Soaked Plasmatic Priest Robe"><br>
<h3>Step 4: Kill Lord Gimblox and return to Timorous</h3>
<p style="color:blue">This step isn't too hard as far as steps go, it's just another long camp. Lord Gimblox spawns in the throne room of SolA. If you sit on the throne facing the way you came in you'll see a PH in the alcove on your left (see image below). That's where Gimblox spawns (loc -796, -366). Your best bet for camping is sitting behind the spawn point in the alcove. The spawn cycle is 19 minutes and everything in here (even the Goblin king) is green so this one can also be done solo. Lord Gimblox himself is a pushover. A few quick nukes and you'll be done. He drops Lord Gimblox's Signet Ring</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul15.jpg" alt="Lord Gimblox"><br>
<u>Level:</u> 30 class unknown<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> Approx. 1800<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> max 76<br>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul16.jpg" alt="Lord Gimblox's Signet Ring"><br>
<p style="color:blue">Now return to Timorous (get used to the long run/swim because this isn't the last time you'll visit here). Hand in your robe to Omat and get your Orb of Frozen Water!</p>
<p><i>Omat Vastsea says "You have proven yourself to be one who is willing to take responsibility for his own actions. Such a trait is desired by all deities to be present in their faithful. I pray that you had the wisdom to slay Lord Gimblox as well as the Plasmatic Priest in order to prevent further advancement in the incursion against the Riptides. Priestess Natasha awaits inside the inn for Lord Gimblox's ring, make haste for she is a busy women and will depart soon"</i></p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul12.jpg" alt="Orb of Frozen Water"><br>
<p style="color:blue">This is the end of this part. Now, obviously, you want to turn in your signet ring ASAP (and we'll cover that in the next part) but know that you won't need the orb in your posession to do most of the rest of the quest so you can bank it.</p>
<h3><a href="index.php?page=epic102">Part 2: Orb of Clear Water</a></h3>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
